sbol:Collection.dcterms:title: iGEM Parts Registry
sbol:Collection.dcterms:description: The iGEM Registry is a growing collection of genetic parts that can be mixed and matched to build synthetic biology devices and systems. As part of the synthetic biology community's efforts to make biology easier to engineer, it provides a source of genetic parts to iGEM teams and academic labs.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_I761012
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: BBa_I761011 is an extracellular glucose concentration controlled promotor. This construct is built to measure the efficiency and threshold extracellular glucose concentration for BBa_I761011. A ECFP gene (BBa_I15016) was put under the control of BBa_R0082 to allow quantitative characterization with spectroscopic method.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: 2007 NYMU_Taiwan iGEM Team
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: Just put any fluorescent reporter gene behind BBa_I761011 and it should have the same function.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: OmpR_BS
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: OmpR binding site. When position behind a promotor, it will turns that promotor into a OmpR controlled promotor. OmpR will function as an inhibitor of that promotor.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: 2007 NYMU_Taiwan iGEM Team
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: This part was derived from BBa_R0082 by PCR.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0032
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Weak1 RBS based on Ron Weiss thesis. Strength is considered relative to <bb_part>BBa_B0030</bb_part>, <bb_part>BBa_B0031</bb_part>, <bb_part>BBa_B0033</bb_part>.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Vinay S Mahajan, Voichita D. Marinescu, Brian Chow, Alexander D Wissner-Gross and Peter Carr IAP, 2003.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
Varies from -6 to +1 region from original sequence to accomodate BioBricks suffix ("RBS-2" in figure 4-14 of thesis).

Contact info for this part: Brian Chow
